|first=Ken|last=Ivan|pos=K}}\n}}\n{{American football roster/Footer|roster_url=|accessdate=\n|head_coach=\n*[[Ara Parseghian]]\n|asst_coach=\n*Tom Pagna (OC)\n*John Ray (DL)\n*Joe Yonto (OL)\n}}\n\n==Game summaries==\n\n===Wisconsin===\n{{Americanfootballbox\n|bg=\n|bg2=\n|titlestyle={{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Notre Dame Fighting Irish|border=2}}; text-align:center\n|state=collapsed\n|title=Notre Dame Fighting Irish (0\u20130) at Wisconsin Badgers (0\u20130)\n|date=September 26\n|time=1:30 pm\n|road=Notre Dame\n|R1=3 |R2= 10|R3=0 |R4=18\n|home=Wisconsin\n|H1=0 |H2=0 |H3=7 |H4=0\n|stadium=[[Camp Randall Stadium]] \u2022 [[Madison, Wisconsin]]\n|attendance=64,398\n|weather=Rain\n|referee=\n|TV=\n|TVAnnouncers=\n|reference=[http://archives.nd.edu/Football/Football-1964s.pdf Notre Dame Football Archives]\n<!--see below|scoring=-->\n|stats=\n{{Col-start}}\n{{Col-2}}\n;Notre Dame\n*[[John Huarte]]<br>15/24, 270 Yds, 2 TD\n*[[Jack Snow (American football)|Jack Snow]]<br>9 Rec, 217 Yds, 2 TD\n{{Col-2}}\n;Wisconsin\n{{Col-end}}\n}}\n\nIn [[Ara Parseghian]]'s coaching debut for Notre Dame, the players carried Parseghian off the field while the Irish fans in attendance chanted \"We're number one\" following the victory.\n\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=ND|HomeName=WIS|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=0:06\n| Team=Notre Dame\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=31\n| Kicker=Ken Ivan\n| Visitor=3\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=\n| Team=Notre Dame\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Jack Snow (American football)|Jack Snow]]\n| QB=[[John Huarte]]\n| yards=61\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=\n| 2pt type=run/pass\n| 2pt result=good/failed/incomplete\n| Visitor=10\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:18\n| Team=Notre Dame\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=\n| Kicker=Ken Ivan\n| Visi