}\n{{College Football National Champion navbox}}\n\n[[Category:1964 NCAA University Division independents football season|Notre Dame]]\n[[Category:Notre Dame Fighting Irish football seasons]]\n[[Category:1964 in sports in Indiana|Notre Dame Fighting Irish]]\n\n\n{{Collegefootball-1960s-season-stub}}\n{{Indiana-sport-team-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |year=1964\n  |team=Notre Dame Fighting Irish\n  |image=Notre Dame Fighting Irish logo.svg\n  |image_size=150 px\n  |conference=Independent\n  |division=\n  |short_conf=\n  |CoachRank=3\n  |APRank=3\n  |record=9\u20131\n  |conf_record=\n  |head_coach=[[Ara Parseghian]]\n  |hc_year  = 1st\n  |off_coach=\n  |oc_year  =\n  |def_coach=\n  |dc_year  =\n  |captain = [[Jim Carroll (American football)|Jim Carroll]]\n  |off_scheme =\n  |def_scheme =\n  |stadium=[[Notre Dame Stadium]]<br>(c. 59,075, grass)\n  |champion=\n  |bowl=\n  |bowl_result=\n}}\n{{1964 NCAA University Division independents football records}}\nThe '''1964 Notre Dame Fighting Irish football team''' represented the [[University of Notre Dame]] during the [[1964 NCAA University Division football season]]. John Huarte was the sixth Notre Dame player to win the [[Heisman Trophy]]. They were crowned national champions by the National football Foundation at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.heisman.com/winners/j-huarte64.html |publisher=heisman |title=1964 Heisman award |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090625232320/http://www.heisman.com/winners/j-huarte64.html |archivedate=25 June 2009}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 1964\n| poll = AP\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 26\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[1964 Wisconsin Badgers football team|Wisconsin]]\n| site_stadium = [[Camp Randall Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Madison, WI]]\n| score = 31\u20137\n| attend = 64,398\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| 